meanings.definition: Print (additional text or images) on top of an existing print.
meanings.sent1: I will overprint the logo on the t-shirt.
meanings.sent2: The company decided to overprint the new information on the old brochure.
meanings.sent3: The printer accidentally overprinted the same page twice, creating a funny effect.
meanings.sent4: Her laughter seemed to overprint the room, filling it with joy.
meanings.sent5: The artist carefully overprinted the signature to ensure it stood out.

meanings.definition: A printed mark or image that is added on top of an existing print.
meanings.sent1: The overprint on the poster caught my eye.
meanings.sent2: She collected stamps with unique overprints from different countries.
meanings.sent3: The overprint of a smiley face on the document made everyone chuckle.
meanings.sent4: The overprint of stars on the sky seemed to twinkle brighter that night.
meanings.sent5: The overprint of flowers on the fabric gave it a lovely touch.
